an Track Record of Success: We have grown every year since our founding in 1993. For additional company information, please visit: www.mtsi-va.com Responsibilities: You will work in a small, highly empowered team where every team member is directly responsible for the success of the program. Engineering responsibilities span technology domains including space rated hardware, software, sensors, and processors in an extremely fast-paced, responsive development environment. Additionally, you will serve as a core point of contact for industry and work directly with subject matter experts across the space domain to quickly converge on solutions that meet warfighter requirements. You must apply advanced principles, theories, and concepts for highly classified systems, while also effectively communicating complex results with management and executive leadership. SETA Role and Responsibilities: Employ highly specialized knowledge or experience to anticipate problems Provide technical assistance to support prime contractor configuration management and requirements management processes Provide analysis of contractor provided artifacts and advice/recommendations system design reviews, subsystem design, software design, test, risk management, and integration activities Conduct technical analyses and risk assessment in a specialized and accelerated acquisition framework Provide technical assistance in developing, refining, decomposition, allocation, and verification of requirements Lead improvements to program progress, technical soundness, and timeliness Manage related market research, R&D studies, and analysis Provide accurate technical guidance, direction, and advice and perform technical reviews within the organization in a timely and effective manner Analyze and apply system engineering and technical management processes at the component, system, or systems-of-systems levels Communicate clearly, concisely, and with technical accuracy\u2014oral and written Qualifications: Required Qualifications: Minimum ten (10) total years of relevant DoD/IC system engineering experience Experience in ground C2 networking, space ground systems, and/or highly autonomous unmanned systems Experience developing, deploying, and maintaining ground mission planning architecture and software Motivated self-starter who can work both independently and in a collaborative team environment, often with minimal guidance and within rigid timelines Strong analytic and critical thinking skills with ability to apply these in a multi-tasking environment where more than one project may require participation simultaneously Outstanding communication skills in conveying complex technical issues and in providing comprehensive written, oral, and/or digital products/presentation development skills Desired Qualifications: Experience working with, or within Industry on DoD related programs System Engineering Technical Assistance (SETA) to Government program office Experience in system engineering of DoD C2 systems Experience in planning and executing test campaigns for space ground systems Knowledge of Defense Acquisition System (DoDI 5000.02) and PPBE process Experience in DoD program management Experience with Integrated Master Schedules, Statements of Work (SOW), Performance Work Statements (PWS), and risk management Fluency with IC organizations Education - Minimum Qualifications: Bachelor's degree from an ABET accredited institution in a related technical field Education - Desired Qualifications & Experience: Relevant PhD degree plus 10 years of related system experience, OR Relevant Master of Science, physics, mathematics, computer science, or engineering degree plus of 20 years of related system experience, OR Relevant Bachelor's degree in physics, mathematics, computer science, or engineering plus 30 years of related system experience Clearance Requirements: Current TS/SCI (SCI eligibility) with SAR/RSV experience within last 5 years, and candidate must maintain a TS/SCI clearance as a condition of employment. Location/Travel Requirements: Full-time, on site in vicinity of Kirtland AFB, NM, and will require travel up to 30% of time within the continental United States. #LI-MR1 ",
